Commented on #374 Github Actions Error: "WARNING: WAT: Could not update filesystem"

Turns out Godot doesn't like case-sensitive folder path names. I had my tests folder named "Tests", however even though WAT was looking for "res://Tests", it still couldn't find the tests folder. Changing the folder in WAT's settings back to "res://tests" fixed it. It's weird that I didn't have to renamed the Tests folder in the end -- I only had to change any loading calls (like file.Open, GD.Load , etc.) to use the lowercase name.
Revert back to snake case for loading
